beer.beer_description:
DIPA

Celebrating our 3rd Birthday 
with a juicy Double IPA, 
brewed in collaboration with 
Banks Brewing. It pours with a 
beautiful thick milky hazy. 
Featuring Citra, Peacharine
and a new experimental hop 
HBC 1019. Expect clouds of 
aromas of sweet peaches and 
citrus fruits with a nice big 
velvety and creamy mouthfeel.

Brewed in Traralgon
beer.beer_style: IPA - Imperial / Double New England / Hazy

Decent hop aroma; peach citrus with an odd cut green herbal character
Smooth fluffy texture with full body
Flavour is very much peach/stonefruit touch of melon & that odd green herb/soapy kind of note
Not really my cup of tea but well executed
